Travel feedback of the week: January 2-8
Readers offer their feedback on travel stories and issues, including Chopin's Majorca and the Burj Al Arab hotel in Dubai. Chopin's Majorca: one reader enjoyed retracing the composer's trip to the Spanish island
11:14AM GMT 08 Jan 2010
Comments
A deserving winner
What a wonderful article Francis Phillips wrote for your Just Back writing competition (December 12) about a day trip to London with his daughter. It was so refreshing after tales of the Sahara, Amazon and the Wall of China. I was in tears after reading the last sentence. Thank you for choosing it. Kath Brett, by email Skiing in Poland
With regard to Adrian Bridge's article ("Skiing with divine guidance", January 2), Zakopane is cheap and a lovely place to start skiing. A taxi ride from Kraków is about £40 and takes about an hour and a half, but it is much cheaper by train. The main problem with the skiing is that the three areas (all a bit limited by Alpine standards) are not connected other than by bus and the inconvenience of getting from one to another is very frustrating. Still, combined with a visit to the lovely city of Kraków, three days in Zakopane is a good experience. Alex Fogwill, website comment
